    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Bar Graph 1: Landscape of Arts Education Nonprofits\"\nauthor: \"Steven Todd McIntyre II\"\ndate: \"2026-02-25\"\nruntime: shiny\nformat: \n  dashboard:\n    embed-resources: true\n    theme: minty\n    output:\n      orientation: columns\nexecute:\n  warning: false\n  message: false\n  echo: false\n---\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n# Overview\n\n## Column\n**How useful can NTEE Codes be in Studying Nonprofits?**\n\nThis dashboard will explore United States nonprofit organizations that are coded as \"A25\" in the National Taxonomy of Exempt Organizations (NTEE), a coding scheme that describes kinds of nonprofit organizations. \"A25\" is defined by the Urban Institute as \"Organizations that provide informal arts educational programming and/or instruction but do not grant diplomas or degrees; or which offer services regarding the arts to educational institutions or to public entities involved in education.\" Using data from the [Urban Institute's Business Master File (BMF)](https://urbaninstitute.github.io/nccs/datasets/bmf/), I explore the kinds of organizations that use A25 \n\n# Visualization 1: A25 Word Count\n\n## Column\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-0ebdcaad255cc06da14b\" style=\"width:100%;height:406px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-0ebdcaad255cc06da14b\">{\"x\":{\"data\":[{\"orientation\":\"v\",\"width\":[957,1842,174,57,66,106,147,72,55,307,98,52,98,59,91],\"base\":[48.549999999999997,49.549999999999997,37.549999999999997,13.550000000000001,18.550000000000001,29.550000000000001,32.549999999999997,20.550000000000001,11.550000000000001,41.549999999999997,27.550000000000001,7.5499999999999998,28.550000000000001,15.550000000000001,25.550000000000001],\"x\":[478.5,921,87,28.5,33,53,73.5,36,27.5,153.5,49,26,49,29.5,45.5],\"y\":[0.90000000000000568,0.90000000000000568,0.90000000000000568,0.89999999999999858